snippet.textDisplay: I'm literally bawling rn. Idk if anyone will read this. But I remember when you posted your first video about Bunny. I was 8 and a half months pregnant. I was MISERABLE. I had a huge cavity and a partially pulled tooth that no other dentist would touch on an 8 month pregnant lady. I was in unbearable pain and the only medicine that helped me, I couldn't take because you cant take ibuprofen when your pregnant.  But you could take fucking lortabs. I felt like such a horrible momma. I had just taken one of my pain killers. I was in my older sons room crying on an air matress. Oh yeah we had no furniture because I found freaking Bed bugs on my beds and couches and I just took it all to the dump. I was horribly depressed and anxious about my baby being born into a bare bones house with me and my tooth pain. And so anxious that any medicine I took would hurt him. I remember being in pain and uncomfortable. And that video was a long one. And for a good while I just zoned out and watched you bring home this baby. Then a month later. In a house with new bug free furniture lol. I brought home an 8 lb baby boy. He just turned 9 months old. Oh God and i am in LOVE. hes perfect. Mamas baby through and through. At that time it felt like hours took days and days took weeks. That last month took a whole damn year. Then since then it's gone by soooo fast. I'm just emotional being that my baby boy is almost a year old. I'm on my period and cramping and its late. And here I am again. Watching a video about your sweet baby. Checking in on mine because hes just so damn sweet to watch and  I am so fucking thankful he is mine 😭😭. Thank you for your wholesome content. I know you dont think it's much sometimes.but we love you and julienne and your dogs so much. I know its helped me. that day specifically. Thank God that day is over lol. But thanks for filling in one of those day long hours when I really needed it.
